  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Presence of large gaps in the delayed enhancement MRI (DE-MRI)</measure>
    <time_frame>3 months</time_frame>
    <description>The presence of MRI ablation gaps around the pulmonary veins evaluated with MRI images of the patient acquired three months after the ablation procedure. A large gap is described as a GAP that is larger or equal than 20% of the vein perimeter.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
